<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
But we can dream right?<P>The way resistances are figured in right now, any percentage has a dispproportionate effect on longer lasting CC.<P>15% reduction on a 10 second mez is less then 2 seconds. 15% redcution on a 60 second mez is a full 9.<P>With the new mez radius code in, a 100% time reduction will now be common.<BR>50%- placement, 30%+ item/buff, 30% from Determ2 = &lt;&gt;100%<P>So why spec high? 100% reduction of a 1.2 minute mez is the same as a 100% reduction of a 10 second mez, but you paid much, much more in spec points to get the higher level version.<P>So what I would propose is a change to the way resists work for CC. Every % point of resistance reduces the duration by .5 seconds. So even 100% resistance would reduce it only by 50 seconds. This would benefit the higher level mezzes, as no matter what, they would beat the 50 seconds unless the enemy PAID for it by spending RA points to get even higher levels of determination.<P>34 points = 75%, so at the edge of a mez (50+75+20)/2 = 70+ seconds off would mean that they could shrug off almost any mez, but they actually earned that right to do so themselves, and not by bitching at Mythic to make us worse.<P>And as mentioned in another post, this would greatly reduce the effectiveness of insta mezzes, as you would just need 62% to annul the highest bard insta.
</FONT>
